column5: Hit some of the fav. spots .....only saw one fish(better than none).  Worked hard for it but managed to pull it off a weedbed.  43 x 18.5"  Took a while to revive it but she swam off strong      Conditions were awesome, i was surprised we did't see more  Matt
Great colours on that fish, Matt. Congrats to you.
Attaboy Matt.   Looks great and crongrats to ya !!
WTG Matt, that's a real purdy fish !!  I'm gonna be up your way in a few weeks lookin for that girls momma, probably about 30 minutes east of you.
Lew   As I said at the Odyssey...call me up if you'ld like and we could hook up , or at least give you some tips and spots.  M.
Matt we will find her Momma next weekend!  nice fish!
Nice musky! Almost tiger musky-like markings.  ehg

Great report...and one very nice muskie!  I was out on Stoney Lake on the weekend, and had one sighting (below the boat) and only one follow.  Conditions there also seemed prime.  Ended up catching bass instead...LOL.
